    {
      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000102837,
      "SummaryText": "Risk Management Plan - Executive Summary\n\nFacility:  MFA Anhydrous Plant Perryville\nLocation:  3501 South Hwy 61, Perryville, Mo. 63775\nContact:  Brian Myers\nPhone:  573-547-2547 \n\n1. The Facility Policy\n\nMFA Incorporated and the employees of the MFA Anhydrous Plant Perryville are committed to the prevention of any accidental release of anhydrous ammonia. If an accidental release should occur, the facility is prepared to work with the Southeast Missouri LEPD and other authorities to mitigate any release and minimize the impact of the release to people and the environment.\n\n2.  Stationary Source and Regulated Substance Handled\n\nThe facility operates an anhydrous ammonia storage facility and sells the regulated substance, anhydrous ammonia, for direct application as a crop nutrient.\n\n3.  The Accidental Release Prevention Program\n\nThe Accidental Release Prevention Program for the location consists of following the provisions of:\na.\t40 CFR Part 68\nb.\tOSHA 29 CFR 1910.111\nc.\tMissouri Anhydrous Ammonia Law\nd.\tCGA G.2.1 - 2023\n\n4. The Five-year Accident History\n\nThere have been no accidental releases of anhydrous ammonia in the past five years that: have caused any deaths, injuries, or significant property damage at the facility; nor to our knowledge, have resulted in offsite deaths, injuries, evacuations, sheltering in place, property damage, or environmental damage.\n\n5. The Emergency Response Program\n\nThe facility has;\n\na. a written emergency action plan, in accordance with OSHA Standard, 29 CFR 1910.38;\n\nb. provided State and Local authorities with the emergency planning and community\n   right-to-know information as required under SARA Title III (EPCRA);\n\nc. employees will not respond to any release other than to activate emergency shutoff valve(s)\n   while evacuating the facility if it is safe for them to do so.  Local responders will be notified\n   to control any release.\n\n6.  Planned Changes to Improve Safety\n\nSafety improvement is an on-going process at the facility"
    }
  ]
